                            <comment id="17001221" author="ctargett" created="Fri, 20 Dec 2019 21:36:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=noble.paul&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;noble.paul&quot;&gt;noble.paul&lt;/a&gt;, this was reopened, did you resolve the failure? If so, can this be Resolved again?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17144385" author="dsmiley" created="Wed, 24 Jun 2020 20:57:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jbernste&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jbernste&quot;&gt;jbernste&lt;/a&gt;&#160;just curious; if the ExportTool had been written as a trivial streaming expressions app, wouldn&apos;t the &quot;per shard&quot; parallel stuff added in this issue be something we might have &quot;for free&quot;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17145132" author="joel.bernstein" created="Thu, 25 Jun 2020 17:23:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This an interesting question. The streams that merge other streams such as &lt;b&gt;parallel&lt;/b&gt; or &lt;b&gt;merge&lt;/b&gt; require a sort order to perform the merge sort. But it would be fairly easy to write a stream that merges without concern about document order.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That being said the &lt;b&gt;topic&lt;/b&gt; can be used to export entire collections and all field types. This is used for the &lt;b&gt;reindex&lt;/b&gt; collection command. Writing to disk could be done with a command line wrapper around &lt;b&gt;daemon(topic(...))&lt;/b&gt;&#160;to write exports to disk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17145689" author="joel.bernstein" created="Thu, 25 Jun 2020 17:33:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Maybe I&apos;ll add a simple command line tool for running streaming expressions stored in files. The output would just be to standard out so it can be piped around.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
bin/expr http:&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//localhost:8983/solr/col/stream file.exp &amp;gt; data.out &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17893452" author="epugh" created="Mon, 28 Oct 2024 13:32:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;FYI, in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-14673&quot; title=&quot;Add CLI for Streaming Expressions&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-14673&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-14673&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; I&apos;ve added a bin/solr stream tool.&#160;&#160; The idea of using Streaming under the covers in the bin/solr export is an interesting one...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
